{"questionId":"17464","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\\left( x \\right) = {p^x} + q\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>p</mi>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>q</mi>\n</math></span>, for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x{\\text{, }}p{\\text{, }}q \\in \\mathbb{R}{\\text{, }}p > 1\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>q</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>. The point&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\\left( {0{\\text{, }}a} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>A</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;lies on the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = {g^{ - 1}}\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>g</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.&nbsp;The point <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>B</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> lies on the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> and is the reflection of point <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>A</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> in the line <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = x\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the coordinates of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\"> <mrow> <mtext>B</mtext> </mrow> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\\left( {a{\\text{, }}0} \\right)\"> <mrow> <mtext>B</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mi>a</mi> <mrow> <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext> </mrow> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; (accept&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\\left( {q + 1{\\text{, }}0} \\right)\"> <mrow> <mtext>B</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mi>q</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mrow> <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext> </mrow> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A2</strong></em><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17464","referenceCode":"19N.1.SL.TZ0.S_10a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down the coordinates of B .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.4—Tangents and normal","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.2—Functions, notation domain, range and inverse as reflection","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.10—Solving equations graphically and analytically","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.5—Intro to logs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}